lead_paragraph: A Federal district judge today rejected an effort by developers to prevent the Interior Department from listing the California gnatcatcher as an endangered species. Such a listing could mean that development could be restricted where the birds live. The department has said it may seek a comprmise on the issue. The developers sought a restraining order to force a review of the scientific data on which the Government decision will be based.
